      <ResourceHeader>
         <ResourceName>Surface meteorological data at Pontianak (GIF format)</ResourceName>
         <ReleaseDate>2016-07-21T18:22:00</ReleaseDate>
         <Description>The time-series plot of surface meteorological data taken by the Automatic Weather Station (AWS) at Pontianak in West Karimantan, Indonesia (0.00S, 109.37E, 1m MSL), which has been operated on March 16, 2008. This plot includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind velocity, wind direction and rain amount. File names are composed of (year)(month)(day).gif (daily plot), (year)(month).gif (monthly plot) and (year).gif (yearly plot). Local time (UT + 07:00) is used for time data.</Description>
         <Acknowledgement>If you acquire surface meteorological data, we ask that you acknowledge us in your use of the data. This may be done by including text such as surface meteorological data were obtained by the JEPP-HARIMAU and SATREPS-MCCOE projects promoted by JAMSTEC and BPPT under collaboration with RISH of Kyoto University and BMKG. We would also appreciate receiving a copy of the relevant publications.</Acknowledgement>
